                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d544">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.61383/140: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-25T19:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 25</hi> [<hi rend="italic">26</hi>], <hi
                                rend="italic">1919, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received October 27, 12.08 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3245. Hanna telegraphed Oct. 26, 4 p.m. that Jenkins had just telegraphed him
                    from within federal lines and soon would be in Puebla. Ransom was carried to
                    rebel lines this morning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
